About

let me introduce myself...


Hello! My name is Danielle Orley, and I’m a detail oriented Full-Stack Web Developer. I recently earned a certificate in web development, from the University of Washington. At the moment, I'm a Washington-based freelancer. Taking in new clients from all over the world. I want to keep learning and push myself to be a better web developer. I take pride in my work and the websites I’ve worked on. Working in the military, retail, and quality control, has taught me to stay calm, react quickly, and take initiative. I’m a hard worker and strive for excellence.

I have a diverse set of skills, ranging from front-end development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) all the way to back-end development(Express, Node.js, PHP). I'm getting more comfortable with technologies like MongoDB and MySql. Right now I like the React JavaScript Library. I’m always learning and experimenting with different languages and tools, and I never get bored. On my home page you can see some of my completed websites. If you want to get ahold fill out the form below or email me.

); } export default About;
